<br>
Grouped with him, Shaman, 2 Rogues (I'm sure Dixxy will add something to this), and a Wizard.<br>
<br>
First of all, it took 30 fucking minutes for him to get his Adventure stone.  We kept repeatedly telling him what to tell the person to get his stone, and he kept saying things like, &quot;Uh...&quot;, &quot;What?&quot; and repeatedly misspelling the text triggers.  I should have left then, but...<br>
<br>
The first two mobs we pull are Warrior and Cleric mobs.  Seerynx, who did not know how to gain and maintain aggro, was tanking the Warrior and the Cleric mob kept CHealing the mob.  Since we had no mezzer, and I was getting LoM from healing groupies and myself because they/I got aggro (due to Seerynx not being able to tank) I suggested we Root the Cleric mob and move the other one back.  After spamming &quot;IF YOU DON'T MOVE THE MOB I'M GATING AFTER THESE TWO ARE DEAD&quot; at least 20 times, the Wizard (who I must commend) chain nukes and kites that Cleric mob around (again wasting my mana because I had to heal him and tank) and kills it.  Finally we kill the other mob and I'm at 0m (after only 2 mobs), so I gate.  Yeah, I admit it, but who would have fucking stayed after that?<br>
<br>
Personally, I wouldn't group with Seerynx at all.  Had a BoT group with him prior to the LDoN group and, well, he sucked. <p>Jawn Doh<br>
